I recently started a new .NET 5 MVC project and wanted to use `dotnet-watch` and the integrated live reload functionality instead of my middleware component. 

Live Reload works with my middleware component enabled.

So I removed it, and just used `dotnet-watch` to run the application expecting the same behavior without the middleware. However, I see no browser refresh and there's no injected JavaScript code or script link that should be there to handle the live reload refresh code on the client.

I can't find any instructions anywhere on how this is supposed to work. Is this functionality enabled by default or is there some switch (there should be if there's not).  

*updated*

I created another brand new project and ran that immediately after creation and that did kind of worked:

* Live Reload works for Razor Views (MVC in my case)
* Live Reload does not work for: HTML, CSS, JS files

In short it works for a new project, but not for my project (startup code below).

